Jeśli nadal pusto, sprawdź jeszcze jedną rzecz: funkcja SQL get_items_nearby musi zwracać created_by_device_id.

W Supabase SQL Editor uruchom:

select *
from get_items_nearby(52.4064, 16.9252, 3000);
Sprawdź, czy w wyniku jest kolumna:

created_by_device_id
Jeśli jej nie ma, filtr w React nie ma na czym działać. Wtedy trzeba poprawić funkcję get_items_nearby.


nie ma

Myślał przez 5s
Trzeba poprawić RPC get_items_nearby, żeby zwracała kolumnę created_by_device_id.

W Supabase SQL Editor uruchom najpierw:

drop function if exists public.get_items_nearby(double precision, double precision, integer);
Potem wklej nową wersję:

create or replace function public.get_items_nearby(
  user_lat double precision,
  user_lng double precision,
  radius_m integer default 3000
)
returns table (
  id uuid,
  title text,
  description text,
  category text,
  condition text,
  size text,
  latitude double precision,
  longitude double precision,
  status text,
  created_at timestamptz,
  expires_at timestamptz,
  distance_m double precision,
  image_urls text[],
  reserved_until timestamptz,
  reserved_by text,
  taken_at timestamptz,
  created_by_device_id text
)
language sql
stable
as $$
  select
    i.id,
    i.title,
    i.description,
    i.category,
    i.condition,
    i.size,
    i.latitude,
    i.longitude,
    i.status,
    i.created_at,
    i.expires_at,
    st_distance(
      i.location,
      st_makepoint(user_lng, user_lat)::geography
    ) as distance_m,
    coalesce(
      array_agg(ip.image_url order by ip.created_at)
        filter (where ip.image_url is not null),
      '{}'
    ) as image_urls,
    i.reserved_until,
    i.reserved_by,
    i.taken_at,
    i.created_by_device_id
  from items i
  left join item_photos ip
    on ip.item_id = i.id
  where
    i.expires_at > now()
    and i.status <> 'taken'
    and st_dwithin(
      i.location,
      st_makepoint(user_lng, user_lat)::geography,
      radius_m
    )
  group by
    i.id,
    i.title,
    i.description,
    i.category,
    i.condition,
    i.size,
    i.latitude,
    i.longitude,
    i.status,
    i.created_at,
    i.expires_at,
    i.location,
    i.reserved_until,
    i.reserved_by,
    i.taken_at,
    i.created_by_device_id
  order by distance_m;
$$;
